  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Optimizing Assessment for All in Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Optimizing Assessment for All project is designed to support countries to improve assessment and teaching of 21st century skills. The project will engage three countries in the Sub-Saharan Africa region notably Democratic Republic of Congo, the Gambia, and Zambia to develop, administer, and pilot classroom-based assessments of 21CS. Its purpose is to strengthen education systems&apos; capacity to integrate 21CS into their teaching and learning; increase assessment literacy among regional and national education stakeholders; develop capacity among teachers on the use of classroom-level assessment of 21CS to support learning; and develop best practices for teaching and learning of 21CS.</narrative>
  </description>
